//Lateral meniscus variant


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - Ligaments, joint capsule & menisci of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Lateral meniscus variant' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Discoid meniscus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pars intermedia, wavy representation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Physiological T2w hyperintensity at meniscal base' checkbox is enabled
And 'Meniscal ossicle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Absent meniscus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Marked volume reduction of the lateral meniscus' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Discoid meniscus' checkbox
Then 'Type 1, complete' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 2, incomplete' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 3, Wrisberg variant' radio button is enabled
When I select 'Type 3, Wrisberg variant' radio button
Then 'Dislocation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening of the posterior meniscofemoral ligament' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Physiological T2w hyperintensity at meniscal base' checkbox
Then a multiple selection localizer is enabled
When I select 'AMVH' part on the Localizer
Then 'AMVH' part is selected and turns red
When I select 'AMPI' part on the Localizer
Then 'AMPI' part is selected and turns red
When I select 'AMHH' part on the Localizer
Then 'AMHH' part is selected and turns red

When I select 'Meniscal ossicle' checkbox
Then a multiple selection localizer is enabled
When I select 'AMVH' part on the Localizer
Then 'AMVH' part is selected and turns red
When I select 'AMPI' part on the Localizer
Then 'AMPI' part is selected and turns red
When I select 'AMHH' part on the Localizer
Then 'AMHH' part is selected and turns red
